[Claude]: Based on my investigation, I can now identify and submit the vulnerabilities. The code shows clear unbounded memory allocation based on untrusted length fields from ASN.1 encoded data.

The critical vulnerability is at line 1671 where `readFromStream(substrate, size, options)` is called with `size = firstOctet & 0x7F` - an untrusted value extracted directly from the input data. This value is then used to allocate memory without validation. The comment at line 1673 even acknowledges this: "missing check on maximum size".

